main event: Two saucer-like objects with red and white flashing lights were observed in the sky for 45 minutes in Wooster, Ohio on 4-22-57 at 23:30.
interesting points: The objects were observed for a significant duration of 45 minutes, allowing for detailed analysis.
The report mentions an unidentified red object traveling at high speed at 300 ft elevation, reported from Worchester, Ohio.
The conclusion on the disposition form suggests that the objects were probably stars, but the data was inconclusive.
The mention of the objects being saucer-like with flashing lights adds to the typical descriptions of UFO sightings during that time period.
The report was filed under the U.S. Air Force's Project Blue Book, a well-known investigation into unidentified flying objects.
sighted object: Two saucer-like objects with red and white flashing lights
witnesses: Reported by SDO Lt Joseph C Scaglione and an unidentified person from Worchester, Ohio
